	<H4>Bela performs at Art in Romney Marsh, 25th September 2011</H4>
	
	<p>Bela plays at Old Romney's 12th century church St. Clements for the wonderful Art in Romney Marsh festival. <br>St. Clements is Derek Jarman's resting place as well as having featured in the cult 1963 film <i>Dr Syn: The Scarecrow of Romney Marsh</i>. <br>A beautiful array of new artwork (for artists, see festival website) will be displayed in the church.<br><br></p><br><p><a href="http://www.artinromneymarsh.org.uk/"><b>Arts In Romney Marsh</b></a> </p></p><br><p><a href="http://www.youtube.com/watch?v=1635RU5-I9k&feature=related"><b>St. Clements on YouTube: Dr Syn</b></a> </p></p>
