	<H4>Bela Emerson live from October 2010</H4>
	
	<p>Bela takes a break from her manic live schedule for a few months - she'll be back in Autumn 2010<p>In the meantime, you can hear her here (visit <a href="http://www.belaemerson.com/shop.html">shop</a> & <a href="http://www.belaemerson.com/music.html">music</a>), on her <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/MsBelaEmerson">YouTube channel</a> and as a guest on various other recent recordings: Nick Pynn's Times-acclaimed <a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/Colours-Night-One-At-Time-Orchestra/dp/B002PAQMYQ">Colours of the Night</a>, The Damned's smashing <a href="http://www.amazon.co.uk/So-Whos-Paranoid-Damned/dp/B001HADG12">So Whos Paranoid?</a>, Ergo Phizmiz's epic <a href="htpp://www.headphonica.com/?p=816">Faust Cycle</a> and Philippe Petit & friendss beautiful<a href="http://www.tracerecordings.com/releases.html">Silk-Screened</a>.<p>There'll be updates here periodically, on new film collaborations with Tereza Buskova (<a href="http://www.terezabuskova.co.uk">website</a>  &amp; <a href="http://www.youtube.com/user/buskovatheslav">YouTube</a>) an upcoming live DVD and some  currently-secret new musical collaborations<p>For updates sent to your inbox, go to the <a href="http://www.belaemerson.com/contact.html">contact form</a>, thanks!</p>
	<BR>
	<p></p>
